<br>
Before damage/delay was bad because the damage bonus on a fast weapon was being applied more often and therefore faster weapons did alot more damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
However, now slower weapons get better bonuses.<br>
<br>
Lets take a look at how much bonus damage 2 weapons do<br>
<br>
Weapon 1  Fiery Defender<br>
<br>
35 damage 40 delay<br>
<br>
15 swings per minute unhasted  34 bonus at 60<br>
<br>
If all 15 swings hit (assume they do on both weapons since hit percecntage is the same)<br>
then <br>
<br>
15 hits times 34 damage bonus= <br>
<br>
510 damage frfom bonus per minute from bonus<br>
<br>
Lance of thunder<br>
<br>
52 damage 46 delay<br>
<br>
13 swings per minute<br>
<br>
13 x 40= 520 damage per minute from damage bonus<br>
<br>
so slower weapon actually does MORE damage than faster here from damage bonus but very close to the same amounnt<br>
<br>
since they are this close you can therefore compare them with damage/delay<br>
<br>
lance of thunder is alot better damage wise<br>
<br>
52/46=1.13<br>
<br>
35/40=.875<br>
<br>
and has slightly more damage bonus damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Comments?<br>
